	 ('Eliot Giacopini','7 Coleman Street','2003-10-19','xapplebee2t@thetimes.co.uk','Pathiri Podi','Pathiri is a traditional dish which is exclusive to the palette of the Kerala cuisine. It is a thin rice pancake made of finely ground rice. Pathiri or Pathil is a tasty breakfast/dinner dish, which tastes good with especially non-vegetarian accompaniments. Although it is a staple diet of the Muslim community, primarily in North Malabar, Pathiri has already made its mark across Kerala due to its extreme light texture and melting softness. HandMade Pathiri powder is ground to perfection, making it the perfect ingredient for mouth-watering Pathiris.','Foodgrains, Oil & Masala',12,'2022-06-25',NULL,'created','Xymenes Applebee','07742 Canary Place','1999-05-31','xapplebee2t@canalblog.com'),
